<br>
MB was good to me and many Innoruuk wizards. Missing spells (Sunstrike, Lure of Ice, Xuzl), ST keys, HD tailsmans, White Dragon scale cloaks, Epic staves, nice (monk?) bags, and other drops to sell for horses/gear.<br>
<br>
the farming Inny's MB team did was no different then any other guild or small group of friends. we geared up because of it but just used a differnt method. A method many balked at. We still had to camp/check spawns just like everyone else.<br>
<br>
but of course we were labeled loot whores and various other names because we wanted/needed this stuff. stuff our guild wasnt about to help get because it was 'kunark' and a waste of time. Yet, as benifitial as it was for many and for our guilds, some of them stll hated MB. They cheer as we were wiping to Sont and a 17k MB crit lands and finishs him then boo as we MB sev for spells because some lone warrior heard sev was up but claimes he was 'KSed by the MB team' for his grean scale. whatever, we never KSed or ran anyone over.<br>
<br>
Is MB still usefull? /shrug. a full bar of mana for 6-9k with no AA crit seems 'iffy'. I dont think I'll be training it again anytime soon since my guild is never in kunark. <p><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=562718" target="top"><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://www.geocities.com/beaune414/obiquon5.txt" style="border:0;"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--></a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></div><!--EZCODE CENTER END--><br>
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=orocular>Orocular</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br>  Posts: 63<br> <font color=#ffffff>(2/11/03 8:17 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Okay... solutions</span><hr size=1> Alright... if you want to say MB is fine with how it is now... cool. Your entitled to your opinion.<br>
<br>
Manaburn in its current state has no use to a raiding party whatsoever. None. You can do more damage with spells. Its a stupid wizard that uses his 2.5k - 5.5k mana on a manaburn on something like THO, High Priest, Emperor... outright stupid. The idea behind the manaburn nerf was to put the 'raid' and 'team' concept back into the dragon encounters. That is the problem. Manaburn now has the only use of last resort, and you better have exodus before you MB, because thats the next skill your gonna be useing for your group.<br>
<br>
Possible REALISTIC solutions to manaburn issues. <br>
<br>
1. Reset the timer. 15 seconds is ample. 30 seconds is still harsh, I think 20 seconds is an ample MB recovery limitation. Still retains the raid party requirement VI wants, and gives us back a somewhat useful skill. I would even venture for wizards to use it on raids! Maybe...<br>
<br>
2. Give us the crit back. If your not going to reset the timer, the skill has no use whatsoever to me if it can't crit. Like I said before, I can do more damage in spell damage.<br>
<br>
3. Since manaburn is so gimp anymore... reduce the AA cost for it. Two points is ample cost for an emergency get out of jail free card. How much does Exodus cost? Manaburn should cost about 25% of what exodus does. I see exodus haveing a much more useful purpose.<br>
<br>
My own personal feelings, Manaburn is the last skill I will take for alternate advancement. My resists will be upped, my wisdom will be upped. Then I will put the points into manaburn. I'll take Nexus gate before I take manaburn in its current form. Point blank, there is no use for manaburn in the game as it stands except to exp groups, then your wizard is oom...<br>
