<br>
But thats just a mages opinion :P <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=raystonn>Raystonn</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Channeler</span><br>  Posts: 213<br> <font color=#ffffff>(2/12/03 6:09 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: My take on MB</span><hr size=1> 1 point of damage per point of mana?  Are you insane?  Why would anyone use it?  Honestly, our normal spells do more damage than that and don't require AA points to use.  The fact that you are a mage perfectly explains your post.<br>
<br>
I really want to see crits added back to Manaburn.  In addition, please modify the the timer.  Rather than a simple 1 minute timer to use the skill on a mob, have the mob resist subsequent MB damage at a percentage equal to 60 - (the number of seconds elapsed since the last MB).  This way, Wizards coudl still use MB at the same time.  The first would land for full damage (including possible crits).  The rest would land with 60% of the damage resisted.  The longer you waited before using MB, the less it would be resisted.  After 1 minute, another MB would land for full again.<br>
<br>
I believe the above to be a fair way to limit the exploitation of Manaburn.  Most of all though, I really want to see crits restored to Manaburn.  I have spent a great deal of time gaining levels and looking forward to that skill.  When I saw it become nerfed, my heart was broken.  I would never be able to see those high crits myself.  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :( --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/frown.gif ALT=":("><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
